## What is this?

React 19 + TypeScript on Vite, tested with Vitest, Testing Library and
**fast-check**. The shell component is `src/App.tsx`; presentational logic
lives in pure `src/lib/` helpers (see `classNames.ts`) so it stays
property-testable. Dependency versions are pinned to the platform's known-good
set.

## Quickstart

```bash
npm install        # first commit ships no lockfile; commit package-lock.json,
                   # then use `npm ci` from there on
npm run dev        # dev server (Vite, HMR)
npm test           # Vitest: component + fast-check property tests
npm run typecheck  # tsc --noEmit (strict)
npm run build      # production bundle in dist/
```

{% if layout == 'monolith' %}## CI

These commands are wired into the root smart pipeline per service — no
`.github/` directory exists at this level on purpose.
{% else %}## CI

Three self-contained checks run on every push and PR — **build**, **test**,
**validate** (typecheck) — on Node 22. The platform's reusable workflows are
Python-focused; frontend CI is self-contained per SPEC §14.
{% endif %}

## Testing standard

Every pure helper in `src/lib/` ships with **fast-check property tests** beside
the example tests (`src/lib/*.test.ts`): an oracle property, cleanliness
invariants and idempotence for `cx`. Components get Testing Library smoke tests
(`src/App.test.tsx`).
